, \"from\": 361, \"to\": 480, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 460, \"end\": 470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.6805766541404834e-24, \"text\": \"Brazilians\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is a lot on the line for the South American powerhouse, who has not finished in the top-six of a major tournament since the 2016 Olympics.\", \"from\": 481, \"to\": 625, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 522, \"end\": 530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999991714429393, \"rank\": 4.0474130859289833e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Is Arthur Elias under pressure?\", \"from\": 626, \"to\": 657, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 629, \"end\": 635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King_Arthur\", \"score\": 0.9990852534643379, \"rank\": 0.0009155827364847621, \"text\": \"Arthur\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King_Arthur\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King_Arthur\"}, {\"begin\": 636, \"end\": 641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elijah\", \"score\": 0.9688040069578087, \"rank\": 0.03220052024789496, \"text\": \"Elias\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elijah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elijah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe, but you can not ignore the consistent failure of this team in competitions not organized by CONMEBOL.\", \"from\": 658, \"to\": 766, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 757, \"end\": 765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CONMEBOL\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.742989811022633e-14, \"text\": \"CONMEBOL\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CONMEBOL\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CONMEBOL\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The defeat to the Japanese was the first time in 2024 that As Canarinhas conceded multiple goals in a 90-minute match.\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 886, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 786, \"end\": 794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"score\": 0.9252669658946778, \"rank\": 0.06488311304699491, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They will hope that this defensive record can help propel this team to at least a draw against probably the most technically gifted team in international women's football.\", \"from\": 887, \"to\": 1058, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"IT ALL STARTS WITH MARTA as she plays a beautiful through ball to Ludmila, who finds 22-year-old Jheniffer to give Brazil the lead \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00a7\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00b7 \\u00f0\\u009f\\u00aa\\u0084\\u00f0\\u009f\\u008e\\u00a5@TelemundoSportspic.twitter.com/5hLRN1OgqC  Spain, along with the United States, are the only teams through two matchdays with six points.\", \"from\": 1060, \"to\": 1346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1126, \"end\": 1133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ludmila_of_Bohemia\", \"score\": 0.9753309270576983, \"rank\": 0.025293028507479054, \"text\": \"Ludmila\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ludmila_of_Bohemia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ludmila_of_Bohemia\"}, {\"begin\": 1175, \"end\": 1181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999858254959291, \"rank\": 1.4174704880948456e-05, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Braz